node.text: JC and Henok make time to catch up on their friendship that formed during the first Rate Beer fest and how Omnipollo's intriguing intersection of beer, pop culture and artistic exploration resonates so much with JC. Fast forward today and hear about how @omnipollo beer is available all over the world while at the same time setting down deeper roots in Sweden. We hit refresh on Covered In Puppies, our collaboration DIPA and its drinking beautifully. We miss you Henok & Karl!

node.text:
We'd like to extend a big thank you to everyone that supported this year's @c2cboston clothing drive. Together we nearly doubled last year's numbers, collecting almost 500 individual pieces of donated clothing, accessories, and toys for children in need!

@mrstrillium has done the honors of selecting our five lucky $100 Gift Card raffle winners. We will be reaching out to you shortly to coordinate your prize pickup.

node.text:
Pilsner days are tough to top! We didn't want to run out of our signature lager as Summer wanes, so we're backing it up with freshies to close out a big August (don't worry, September is showing no signs of slowing down).

Order cans at 9 AM for Pick Up and UPS Direct.

How much Nelson is too much Nelson? We haven't hit our limit yet!

We've got a special Saturday release lined up for you with the return of our New Zealand dry-hopped flagship Pale Ale. Cans will become available online tomorrow at 9 AM for both Pickup and UPS Direct.

node.text:
File this under photos we wish you could taste...

Tomato season is in full swing down at the Trillium Farm in North Stonington, CT. We're growing seven varietals this year, ranging in size from cherry tomatoes with incredible flavor concentration to large slicers, like the Marnouar pictured in the first photo. Classics, heirlooms, experimentals - there's some of each!

You can find these beauties currently in the following dishes at our restaurants.

Fort Point:
Summer Kale Salad
Burger

Canton:
Ricotta & Foccacia
Green Bean Salad
'Nduja Pizza
Tomato Salad w/ Mole

Welcome to Fuzz Effect Day!

The latest addition to the Headroom family has arrived and we can't wait for you to try it. Cans are now available to order online for pickup in Canton, Fenway, and Fort Point or have them shipped to any address in MA, DC, KY, NE, NH, PA, or VT.

If you're picking up at any of our locations today, we'd like to kindly ask that you arrive as close to the pickup time assigned to your order as possible. This ensures that wait times are minimal and the overall flow of traffic is better for all.

Let's do this!

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Trillium Brewing Company on August 26, 2021. May be an image of drink.

node.text:
Embrace the distortion!

If you've been following along closely, you've noticed that we've been hooked on Nelson Sauvin throughout 2021. Our selection of the New Zealand varietal has been absolutely brilliant this year, making it the perfect choice for pushing the boundaries of hop saturation in true Headroom fashion.

Boasting an absurd level of dry-hopping, Fuzz Effect makes its debut tomorrow. We're tasting lush tropical smoothie, fresh-pressed white grape juice, and lychee sorbet. It's a silky, palate-coating hop delight. 

Cans will be available to order online tomorrow at 9 AM for both Pickup and UPS Direct. ($22.20) 4-pack, limit one case per person.

node.text:
Tomorrow is shaping up to be a big day! First up, our nod to a timeless, old-fashioned treat.

A precise blend of three distinct base imperial stout recipes, each aged in bourbon barrels between 22-35 months, Barrel-Aged Chocolate Covered Peanut Brittle offers notes of roasted peanuts, bourbon-soaked oak, brown sugar, and much, much more.

Bottles will be available to order online tomorrow at 9 AM for both Pickup and UPS Direct. $24.05/500ml bottle, limit four bottles per person.

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Trillium Brewing Company on August 26, 2021. May be an image of food and indoor.

node.text:
With today's heat, we're craving oysters! 🦪

These Moon Shoal beauties from Barnstable, MA are currently on the menu in Fort Point. Served composed with our Oenobier mignonette, Calabrian chili, and shallot, a half dozen (or more, we don’t judge) is our ideal way of cooling off.

Beginning near Roxbury's Nubian Square, Blue Hill Ave runs south down to Canton where it ends at the door of the Blue Hills Reservation, just over a mile from our restaurant and taproom at 100 Royall Street.

The beer named in its honor, and the latest addition to the Avenue Series, features a substantial addition of one of our favorite PNW hops in Simcoe. We're tasting bright notes of tangelo juice, sugar-dusted grapefruit slices, and pine.

Order cans online tomorrow at 9 am for both Pickup and UPS Direct.
